README.name: Welcome
README.content:
## Welcome! Welcome, this is 'discordjs-economy' module!
discordjs-economy will simplify creating Economy System for Your Discord Bot! [Documentation](https://djs-economy.js.org/) | [Support Server](https://discord.gg/zsTgXs24k2) ### Warning! To use this module You need to have [NodeJS v14 or Above](https://nodejs.org/) installed! ## Features [ðŸ”‘] Built in TypeScript
[âš™] 100% Promise-based
[ðŸ™‚] TypeScript Support
## Installing npm i @badboy-discord/discordjs-economy
yarn add @badboy-discord/discordjs-economy ## This module uses [1] [enmap (Database)](https://npmjs.com/package/enmap/)
[2] [TypeScript (Compiller)](https://npmjs.com/package/typescript/)

changelog.name: ChangeLog
changelog.content:
Information taked from [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/discordjs-economy/source/release) and [Discord Server](https://discord.gg/9Ps78AGadm).
[1.0.0] First Release: - Added 5 Classes - BalanceManager, BankManager, DBManager, Economy, ShopManager (Economy as default) - Added functionality for Database Manager - Added functionality for Balance and Bank Managers - Added functionality for Shop Manager - Created TypeDefs - Created Module Declarations [1.0.1] Fixes and New Methods:
- Fixed and Added some TypeDefs - Changed Pages for Website - Added 'leaderboad()' Method to Economy Class - Added Privated Methods 'init()' and 'checkVersion()' to Economy Class - Added new Option for Version Control - Created ItemsManager Class for Inventory Handling [1.0.2] New Classes:
- Edited and Added some TypeDefs - Created Cooldown and Rewards Managers - Created Objects for Rewards - Edited some methods from Economy Class - Created Typings for new Managers - Created Basic Example for module
